Sigaction Parameters

int sigaction(int signum, const struct sigaction *restrict act, struct sigaction *restrict oldact)

int signum
DESCRIPTION: specifies the signal, and it can be any signal except SIGKILL or SIGSTOP.
POSSIBLE VALUES: all signals except SIGKILL and SIGSTOP.

const struct sigaction *restrict act
DESCRIPTION: this can be NULL or not. If is not NULL, the new action for signal signum is installed from act,
otherwise, it's not. This struct pointer sent by parameter will instruct the action to take to the associated signal.
POSSIBLE VALUES: NULL or struct sigaction variable type.

struct sigaction *oldact
DESCRIPTION: basically, if we send a pointer in this parameter, the previous action will be saved.
POSSIBLE VALUES: NULL and struct sigaction variable type.